				\begin{document}$$3.5\cdot 10^{-3}$$\end{document}) and the insertion losses of the various optical elements (filters, lenses, collimators). Theoretically (Shaklan and Roddier 1988), an increase of the coupling efficiency from telescope to fiber by a factor 100 can be expected, while the use of integrated optics instead of bulk optics relay and higher laser pump powers could increase further the efficiency of the photon conversion stage (overall conversion efficiency 1%).

